-- TVS Motor Surges to Four-Year High in Mumbai Trading on Free Share Plan
-- Siddharth Philip
-- 2010-07-21T09:07:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-21/tvs-motor-surges-to-four-year-high-in-mumbai-trading-on-free-share-plan.html

          
          
             TVS Motor Co. , Indiaâ€™s third-largest
motorcycle maker, surged to the highest level in more than four
years in Mumbai after saying it plans to issue free shares.  
 The company  jumped as much as 13 percent to 137.25 rupees,
the highest intra-day price since May 2006. The stock changed
hands at 133.70 rupees at 1:48 p.m.  
 Chennai, south India-based TVS Motor will give one free
share for every one held, according to a statement today. The
motorcycle maker also said net income in the quarter ended in
June more than doubled to 404 million rupees ($8.5 million)
after sales increased.  
 TVS will also pay an interim dividend of 50 paise per
share, the company said in the statement.  
